POLICE have urged the public to help them trace a 72-year-old Chilean tourist who went missing in Edinburgh earlier today.
Victor Gonzale was last seen around 12 noon on the Water of Leith walkway at Bells Brae with his wife and daughter.
He is around 5ft 8in tall with tanned skin and short white hair, was wearing dark grey trousers, a pink shirt and a beige, brown and blue cardigan.
Victor is Spanish-speaking and does not speak English.
A Police spokesman said: “ Victor has not been in contact with friends or family since then and they are growing increasing concerned for his welfare.
 “Anyone who might have seen Victor or who has information is asked to contact police immediately on 101.” 
